reviews.text: Disappointed in the food temperature, lukewarm after waiting1hr 40min, and was told the garlic knots have garlic on them. Maybe garlic flavored oil, with tons of grated parmesan cheese, but NO GARLIC. They do even have a garlic taste. This is the 2nd time we have ordered in a week and been disappointed both times. Last order was a special request to not make the Stromboli well done, one was fine, the other burnt.  Time to find a new regular place.

I've ordered delivery from here about 7 or so times now, each time the food is fantastic. Had the cheesesteak twice, individual pizza slices twice, and a meatball sub. Whole pizzas the rest of the time, every time it's really great pizza. I keep it simple with just cheese and pepperoni, the sauce is really good it's not too thick  and has a great actual tomato taste. Each time it's been very consistent with is great, I know what I'm getting and it's going to be tasty.

It's really cool to see places doing by the slice again, it wasn't something offered a lot of times but has been making a come back. All the food is great it's never been a bad experience, the subs are probably about 12 inches maybe 14. Never lasted long enough for me to care to get a tape measure and the pricing for delivery is very reasonable.

EDIT: I think I got the brownie from here, it was good.

I brought a 14 inch pepperoni pizza with a brownie and it wasn‚Äôt bad. The pizza did have a unique taste and that is what makes it good and very different. I didn‚Äôt even have to ask for extra pepperoni or get a bit annoyed because there wasn‚Äôt enough pepperoni due to past experiences with pizzerias not giving enough pepperoni. The sauce wasn‚Äôt much and there was more cheese than sauce but that is what makes the pizza unique and the pizza wasn‚Äôt one of those high rising kinds which I find a bit unnecessary. Now the brownie, it was crunchy and creamy and sweet, but I shouldn‚Äôt expect any less because a brownie is a sweet, but anyways the brownie wasn‚Äôt what I thought it would be, but it wasn‚Äôt bad, just crunchy and creamy. I might come back as this was my first time trying out this place.
These guys are our ‚Äúgo to‚Äù place for pizza and cheese steaks! Always super tasty and ready quickly. If you have never given them a try, you should do so. You want be sorry!!

My wife and I each got one of the Italian meals w/ the side salad. They are a delicious option when we decide to not get our favorite pizza in the area. Great Pizza is one of our absolute favorites in Chesapeake.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Olmstead
detailedReviews.text: The food was subpar for the price.  A five cheese pizza with barely any cheese, a bacon chicken ranch pizza was very dry and did not taste like ranch.  The chicken parm. sub had no flavor (especially the sauce).  The French fries and onion rings were soggy and cold.  The ultimate chocolate cake seemed like it had sat in their refrigerator for weeks, because the icing was hard.  I was told it would be an hour for the delivery that took an hour and 45 minutes to arrive.  $100 with tip definitely not going to waste that kind of money on subpar food.  I can normally tell if a restaurant has good food if they have a good chicken parm., but this was the first and last time I will be getting food from here.

My wife asked me a couple of times to try this place, and I told her any place named "The Great Pizza Company" is not gonna have a good pie. Don't let the name fool you! I finally tried it and was pleasantly surprised. (Apologies to the owner, but I hate the name, it delayed me stopping by and giving it a shot). I loved it, and it's now my go-to place to pick up great pizza and garlic knots. Both are the best around. Please don't make a "new and improved" sauce!! LOL.

detailedReviews.author: Lynne W
detailedReviews.text: I'm addicted to their garlic knots and bone in wings. The marinara is the best I've ever had. I've had service from then over a hundred times. They pretty much know what I want and when I call most of the time I don't even have to say my phone number. Staff extremely friendly, and their Eggplant Parmegan Rocks 10.99 comes with a nice salad and garlic knots. Let them deliver.  CALL 277-9922

detailedReviews.author: Lynne
detailedReviews.text:
I love their lasagna lunch special that comes with 2 garlic knots & a drink, their 2 slice lunch special that also comes with a drink and their fried mushrooms. They used to have beer battered onion rings, and that is still how they're described on the menu, but they're now panko OR and I am NOT a fan.

Their delivery is quick and to my location, a buck and let's get real, where else can you get delivery for a dollar.

Oh, skip the tiramisu. It's expensive and on a good day, mediocre.

detailedReviews.author: debby hunt
detailedReviews.text: We LOVE the Great Pizza Co.!  We live close by and probably order from them at least every two weeks and have been doing so for years.  Everything we get from them is delicious!  Personal favorites are the rabbit food pizza (we feel less guilty eating it) and their tiramisu.  They are a hard working place and they delivered all through COVID when we couldn't go out to restaurants as we are seniors...(I hate refering to ourselves that way but it is what it is!)   Thank you Great Pizza Co. for the great food and the great delivery service!

detailedReviews.text: Was just quoted 35-45 minutes and was promptly hung up on before I could order.  What is wrong with customer service now-a-days? Who doesn't have one of the most common types of pizza on the menu?  You can't add pepperoni to a pizza online.  I will never attempt to order from this rude business again.
